Subject: workspace-mcp: pass login_hint on Google consent URL

When the caller already knows which Google account to use
(`user_google_email` is provided to `start_auth_flow`), forward it as
`login_hint` on the authorization URL so Google's consent page
pre-selects that account. Without this, the consent page uses whichever
Google account happens to be signed into the user's default browser
profile, which is often the wrong account for a Cloud project.

Upstream equivalent: github.com/taylorwilsdon/google_workspace_mcp PR #556.
When that merges, revert this patch.

See: docs/adr/0003-direct-google-api-over-n8n.md

--- a/auth/google_auth.py
+++ b/auth/google_auth.py
@@ -515,7 +515,15 @@ async def start_auth_flow(
             required_scopes=current_scopes,
             session_id=session_id,
         )
-        auth_url, _ = flow.authorization_url(access_type="offline", prompt=prompt_type)
+        # LazyClaw patch: pass `login_hint` when the caller already
+        # named an account, so Google pre-selects it on the consent
+        # screen and the user can always click "Use a different
+        # account" to escape. Fixes the "consent opens on wrong
+        # profile" bug — see ADR-0003.
+        auth_kwargs = {"access_type": "offline", "prompt": prompt_type}
+        if user_google_email:
+            auth_kwargs["login_hint"] = user_google_email
+        auth_url, _ = flow.authorization_url(**auth_kwargs)

         store = get_oauth21_session_store()
         store.store_oauth_state(
